Place peas in large pot. Add enough water to cover peas by 2 inches. Bring to boil; boil 2 minutes. Remove from heat. Let stand 1 hour. Add ham meat and bone, onions and pepper flakes to peas. Add enough water to cover peas and meat by 2 inches; cover. Cook on medium heat about 30 minutes or until peas are tender. Add additional water if necessary to keep the peas juicy. Stir in rice; let simmer 20 minutes or until rice is tender. Stir in the pickle relish and Singles.